  "body": "* Project GitHub tag: https://github.com/status-im/status-react/labels/chat-reliability\r\n\r\n### Project Vision\r\n\r\nThe goal of this project is:\r\n* to make messaging extremely reliable;\r\n* to be able to prove that;\r\n* to be able to show that information to a user (especially it is important to\r\n    communicate if the message isn't delivered).\r\n\r\n### Project Scope\r\n\r\n\"Message reliability\" in this project means:\r\n- being able to deliver a user's message;\r\n- or being able to communicate to the user that her message wasn't delivered;\r\n- with the current network topology and level of decentralization.\r\n\r\nThe scope includes research & investigation, creating toolkit to monitor and test reliability.\r\n\r\n### Project Tradeoffs\r\n1. ????\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nSee also: \r\n* https://discuss.status.im/t/diagnosing-chat-reliability-issues/729\r\n* Geth Discussion about Whisper ACKs: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/issues/18159\r\n\r\n\r\n### Why is messaging unreliable?\r\n\r\n- [ ] Message history differs between desktop and mobile for the same user being online at the same\r\n    - [x] https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/7097\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Mailserver requests looks like take long.\r\n- [ ] (golang) https://github.com/status-im/status-go/issues/1279\r\n- [ ] Deploy the changes\r\n\r\n#### History of a particular mailserver might be lost if we upgrading it/installing it\r\n- [x] (in progress, golang) https://github.com/status-im/status-go/issues/1290\r\n- [x] deploy the changes\r\n\r\n#### If a mailserver is down, it takes a long time to figure this out and switch to another one.\r\n- [x] (in progress) https://github.com/status-im/status-go/issues/1285 (mailserver management on status-go side)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Receiving messages from a mailserver (from a user perspective, the time between requesting messages from mailserver and actually rendering new messages) looks suspiciously long. And we have no way of measuring it and splitting into components.\r\n\r\n\r\n#### If there are no new messages received, user doesn't know that he is up to date. There is no way to figure out if the request failed vs. user is up-to-date.\r\n\r\n#### If a topic is crowded (like we witnessed in Prague) the response from the mailserver can quickly consume the data plan from the user. We need to think about ways to mitigate this (maybe request a preview from the mailserver so we can inform the user that messages won't be downloaded automatically for the selected chat if he's on 4G?)\r\n- [ ] (clojure) https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/6758\r\n- [ ] Whisper rate limiting\r\n    - [x] https://github.com/status-im/status-go/pull/1222\r\n    - [ ] (devops) enable whisper rate limiting on mailservers\r\n    - [ ] (clojure) show traffic usage by public channels/whisper topics\r\n\r\n#### We don't have any on-call procedures for when mailservers go down, etc. It is important with the current infrastructure, while we have our cluster.\r\n- [x] Implement a playbook and response procedures for mailserver issues\r\n\r\n#### We don't show the user any information whenever he is missing intermediate messages on a 1:1 chat. \r\n\r\n#### Missing messages for public chats due to Whisper TTL\r\n- [x] (in progress, clojure) https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/6814\r\n\r\n#### Messaging fails on public wifi \r\n- [ ] (golang) #6351\r\n\r\n--- \r\n\r\nDONE\r\n\r\n\r\n#### ~Push notifications being received way before messages are downloaded, leading to \"phantom\" push~\r\n- [x] Messages are marked as \"sent\" erroneously: https://github.com/status-im/status-go/issues/1276\r\n    - [x] ACKs for Whisper: https://github.com/status-im/status-go/issues/1278\r\n    - [x] (in progress, clojure) upgrade status-go && send info about the connected mailserver to status-go https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/6889\r\n\r\n#### ~We don't have any way to check if the message history is consistent on the server side.~\r\n- [x] https://github.com/status-im/statusd-bots/issues/6\r\n- [x] deploy x-check-mailserver: https://github.com/status-im/infra-eth-cluster/issues/20",
